---
description: Enforce accessible Dialog/Sheet title and description requirements
globs: alm-app/frontend/src/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

# Dialog and Sheet Accessibility Rule

- Root cause: Radix `DialogContent`/`SheetContent` logs accessibility warnings when no title is rendered in the content tree. Radix wires `aria-labelledby` to an internal `titleId` and checks `document.getElementById(titleId)`.
- **Never set a custom `id` on `DialogTitle`.** Radix applies `id: context.titleId` first, then spreads your props; a custom `id` overrides the context id, so the check fails and the console shows a false “requires DialogTitle” warning. Use `data-testid` for tests if needed.
- Project safeguard: [`alm-app/frontend/src/shared/components/ui/dialog.tsx`](alm-app/frontend/src/shared/components/ui/dialog.tsx) `DialogContent` injects a screen-reader-only `DialogTitle` when the child tree does not already contain one. Detection unwraps `React.memo` / `forwardRef` around `DialogTitle` so the fallback is not skipped incorrectly. Feature code should still pass an explicit visible or `sr-only` title whenever possible.
- i18next: set `showSupportNotice: false` in [`alm-app/frontend/src/i18n/index.ts`](alm-app/frontend/src/i18n/index.ts) to avoid the default Locize `console.info` on init (unrelated to Radix; often confused with app errors).
- Every `DialogContent` must include a `DialogTitle` in its rendered tree.
- Every `SheetContent` must include a `SheetTitle` in its rendered tree.
- Prefer explicit structure: `DialogHeader` + `DialogTitle` (+ `DialogDescription` when useful).
- Prefer explicit structure: `SheetHeader` + `SheetTitle` (+ `SheetDescription` when useful).
- For `DialogContent`, provide either:
  - an explicit `DialogDescription`, or
  - `aria-describedby={undefined}` when description is intentionally omitted.
- For `SheetContent`, provide either:
  - an explicit `SheetDescription`, or
  - `aria-describedby={undefined}` when description is intentionally omitted.
- If title text must be visually hidden, keep it accessible with `className="sr-only"`.
- Do not merge code that introduces a `DialogContent` without a title; fix it in the same change.
- Do not import Radix dialog primitives directly in feature code; use shared wrappers from `shared/components/ui`.
- App-wide modals: see [`.cursor/rules/modal-system.mdc`](modal-system.mdc) (`ModalManager`, `modalApi`, dismiss-on-navigation).

## Good

```tsx
<DialogContent>
  <DialogHeader>
    <DialogTitle className="sr-only">Create suite</DialogTitle>
    <DialogDescription className="sr-only">Create a suite and configure links.</DialogDescription>
  </DialogHeader>
  ...
</DialogContent>
```

```tsx
<DialogContent aria-describedby={undefined}>
  <DialogHeader>
    <DialogTitle>Compact dialog</DialogTitle>
  </DialogHeader>
  ...
</DialogContent>
```

```tsx
<SheetContent>
  <SheetHeader>
    <SheetTitle className="sr-only">Artifact details</SheetTitle>
    <SheetDescription className="sr-only">View and edit artifact information.</SheetDescription>
  </SheetHeader>
  ...
</SheetContent>
```

## Bad

```tsx
<DialogContent>
  <div>...</div>
</DialogContent>
```
